      "content": "Please consult your obstetrician or midwife immediately before taking any medication, as pseudoephedrine may not be safe for you at 24 weeks. Sinus infections often worsen pregnancy due to nasal congestion from hormonal changes, so discuss safe non-drug options like steam inhalation or saline rinses with your provider. Getting relief is important for your rest, but never self-medicate during pregnancy without medical approval.",
