      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I cannot advise you to take a single dose of pseudoephedrine, because even one dose can constrict blood vessels that are critical for supplying oxygen to your developing baby, potentially causing distress or fetal loss. The risk is real and unpredictable regarding your specific placental health, which is why medical professionals strictly avoid this medication during pregnancy without direct supervision. Please seek a pharmacist or an on-call doctor from your hospital instead of taking a tablet before consulting them.",
      "source": "target",
